<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ESSAYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In his column, Danziger rebukes colleges and universities for encouraging 
insincerity in the youth of America when they write their college application 
essays. 
</P>
<P>
Danziger muses, "What would happen if someone just wrote what he or she was 
thinking?" Well, here's the start of an essay that's not at all phony, one that 
Danziger might like. 
</P>
<P>
 "If you really want to hear about it, the first thing you'll probably want to 
know is where I was born, and what my lousy childhood was like, and how my 
parents were occupied and all before they had me, and all that David 
Copperfield kind of crap, but I don't feel like going into it, if you want to 
know the truth." 
</P>
<P>
 Holden lives! But, then again, he never did do well in school. 
</P>
<P>
SUSAN EDDY 
</P>
<P>
Newport Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
