<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Yields on 30-year Treasury bonds fell at the latest auction to the lowest level 
since August, 1987. The average yield was 8.91%, down from 9.10% at the last 
auction on Nov. 17, 1988. It was the lowest rate since 30-year bonds averaged 
8.89% on Aug. 13, 1987. The bonds will carry a coupon interest rate of 8.875%, 
with each $10,000 in face value selling for $9,963.60. A total of $9.5 billion 
in bonds was sold out of bids totaling $17.2 billion. 
</P>
