<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NBC program chief Brandon Tartikoff, addressing an industry lunch Thursday in 
New York, had a complaint similar to that of Rodney Dangerfield -- no respect. 
Asked to assess the worst part of this season for NBC, he said it's the 
"sometimes exaggerated" knocks NBC has taken for airing some shows critics 
found tasteless or even sleazy. "I'd just like to see a little respect out 
there from the critical community. I think the only person who's had worse 
press than me has been (executed serial murderder) Ted Bundy." ALEENE MacMINN 
</P>
