<TEXT>
<P>
Premier John Swan's conservative United Bermuda Party, which has ruled the 
island for 20 years, held onto power Thursday but its majority in the 44-seat 
House of Assembly was cut from 31 seats to 23. 
</P>
<P>
The left-leaning Progressive Labor Party increased the number of its seats from 
7 to 15, official election results showed. 
</P>
