<HEADLINE>
<P>
USC AND UCLA WOMEN TO MEET TONIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE CART 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The women's basketball teams of USC and UCLA will play tonight at 7 at Pauley 
Pavilion in a game that has more meaning as a sputtering rivalry than in 
determining postseason play. 
</P>
<P>
The Bruins are 9-10 and have lost their last three games. In the Pacific 10 
Conference, they are in fourth place with a 5-4 record, one game out of third. 
</P>
<P>
UCLA has shot only 36% from the field in its last three games. The leading 
scorers are freshman center Molly Tideback (12.7 points) and junior forward 
Sandra vanEmbricqs (12.5 points). 
</P>
<P>
USC, which is 3-6 in conference play, is in a three-way tie for sixth. Cherie 
Nelson is USC's leading scorer at 25.2 points. 
</P>
<P>
The Bruins beat USC, 76-62, in mid-January. JULIE CART 
</P>
</TEXT>
