<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHANG UPSETS CONNORS IN CHICAGO TOURNAMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CHICAGO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sixteen-year-old Michael Chang, capitalizing on numerous unforced errors, upset 
second-seeded Jimmy Connors, 6-3, 7-6, Thursday in a second-round match at the 
$350,000 Volvo Chicago tennis tournament. 
</P>
<P>
After losing his serve in the 11th game of the second set to go down, 5-6, 
Chang broke Connors back to force the tiebreaker, which Chang won, 7-2. 
</P>
<P>
Chang, ranked 29th in the world, is fresh from two Davis Cup wins against 
Paraguay. Connors, 36, is ranked seventh. 
</P>
</TEXT>
