WORLD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Israeli soldiers rounded up about 175 Palestinians in the West Bank and forced 
them to sit blindfolded and bound for up to 16 hours in a soccer stadium, Arab 
and Israeli witnesses said. Many were in their pajamas after being seized 
overnight in Hebron, apparently on suspicion of planning an action against 
Israeli authorities, Israeli sources said. Dozens of the Arabs were later moved 
to detention centers while the rest were sent home, the witnesses said. At the 
United Nations, a spokeswoman said the Security Council, acting on a request by 
Tunisia, will meet today on the continuing violence in the occupied 
territories. 
</P>
