<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY HOSPITAL BIRTHS -- JANUARY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Clipboard researched by Kathie Bozanich, Susan Davis Greene, and Rick 
VanderKnyff / Los Angeles Times. Graphics by Doris Shields / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UCI, St. Joseph and Fountain Valley Regional Hospitals all recorded more than 
400 births during January, to lead delivery room activity at county hospitals. 
The 3,211 births recorded during the first month of the year is nearly a 30% 
increase over the 2,482 births reported in January, 1988. Here's the breakdown 
by individual hospitals: 
